release dates: USA::16 February 2011                            (New York City, New York)

1.title: Nibbling Rivalry
1.plot: Meet three of the ladies who are as crazy for their canines as they are for New York City.

2.title: Love Bites
2.plot: Meet Leslie (SalliSue's mom) this week as she joins up with Erika and Grace to try her hand at some speed-dating-for-dog-lovers romance. And it's not only the men nipping at Leslie's heels. She and Grace bark and bite over dating rules.

3.title: It's My Party and I'll Bark If I Want To
3.plot: Grace outdoes herself when she throws a birthday bash for her beloved Rosie. She involves everyone - including the newest Doggie Mom in town, Ashley - in the prepping and planning. From the pre-party Botox injections to the homemade doggie hors d'oeuvres, Grace goes all out to make herself outshine the guests - even birthday girl, Rosie.

4.title: The Fab Furry Life
4.plot: The Doggie Moms take their act on the road to Greenwich, Connecticut, to rub elbows with the upper crust elite at an exclusive polo event, which includes a dog parade with prizes for the best polo-themed doggie outfit. Watch as the out-of-towner Doggie Moms put their couture doggie designs up against local favorite pooch wear.

5.title: Life Has Gone to the Dogs!
5.plot: It's another busy week for the Moms and their dogs, from Karen and Eli's outdoor photo-shoot with a fashion photographer to Leslie making ends meet by donning a gorilla suit and singing happy birthday. Erika gives Cubby swimming lessons just in time for vacation and all of the Doggie Moms throw a doggie house party. No matter where life takes them, the ladies show us some of the crazy things they do for their dogs.

6.title: All's Fair in Love and Pageants
6.plot: Leslie is knee deep in preparations as she expands her annual Barking Beauty Pageant out of state to New Jersey. Between organizing the event and finding ways to pay the pageant bills, she's got her hands (and Sallisue's paws) full. The main categories: Active Wear, Glamour Wear, and Talent. Will Erika and Cubby keep up their winning streak? And will Grace contain her growling and accept the judges' decisions?

7.title: Reunion Special: Part 1
7.plot: Watch the fur fly as the Doggie Moms break it down in this reunion special, hosted by Toni on New York's very own Toni Senecal.

8.title: Reunion Special: Part 2
8.plot: Watch the fur fly as the Doggie Moms break it down in this reunion special, hosted by Toni on New York's very own Toni Senecal.

imdb.plot outline: Doggie Moms follows a group of New York City women whose lives revolve around their dogs - doggie dates, birthday parties, weddings, meet-ups, pageants, fashion shows, costume contests, fundraisers, you name it. These doggie moms are tenacious about ensuring the best for their babies, pinning all of their hopes and dreams on their four-legged, furry "children." Created by Next Millennium Productions, the six part series features five "moms" as they compete for fame and fortune and jockey for social stature in the doggie world. The moms have a lot of heart too, working tirelessly to give back to the community, raising money for local animal shelters and other charities. Some have even prepared their pets to be therapy dogs who comfort the sick and elderly. The series also serves as a resource for pet owners in the City, sharing details about the guidelines behind licenses, transporting dogs, microchipping, spaying and neutering and more. Episodes look at the importance of grooming and nutrition, adopting shelter pets, pet first aid, how to volunteer to help animals and more.
